#girldrummer #drummergirl #drums #drumcover #drumming #drummer #drumlife #drummersofinstagram #nashvilledrummer #vater #vaterdrumsticks #rolandvdrums #vad507 #td27 #rolanddrums #roland #paramore #paramoreconcert #paramorealbum #thisiswhy #paramorefan

My little corner of the world right in this room 🌎✨ It’s funny when you take a step back and you see the puzzle pieces come together. 

I have played the drums since I was 15 years old, or maybe even earlier, and a few years back some of you may remember that I went full-time freelancing videography. It’s funny looking back on that now, because I learned so much in those few years that I am now applying to my own material. 

I just kind of laugh because that makes total sense, doesn’t it? I love how God works in our favor even when we don’t see it. Eventually, we do see it and even then, I know that he’s not done yet! 

Over the years, I have continually felt the calling to go back to my roots, which has always been music, specifically the drums. What I established on YouTube in the early years, made such a profound mark in my life, through the people that I have met, impacted, and even inspired to pick up drumsticks. But no matter what, everything I did led me back to this point. 

I was working for other people as hard as I could and kept asking myself, “What if you put the amount of time you’re putting into someone else’s dream into YOUR own dream?” I don’t even know what my dream is, but I couldn’t shake that thought. So here I am. In my most “me” form of myself if that makes sense, and I’m excited to see where it all takes me.

Thank you for your continued support.

Bring me back to Grenada 🇬🇩 Wes and I can confidently say we’ve found our new favorite spot where everything is perfect! The diving, the beaches, the people, the fresh fish, the sweetest fruit, the amazing music, and the incredible sights. A trip we will never forget, and we will have to absolutely come back. Also special thanks to Travis and the amazing dive team at Sandals Grenada for bringing me on my first wreck dive. Footage of the dives to come soon…
Take us back to the pool please! 🌴🇬🇩🌊

First one in the water ✌🏻🤿🐠 Also, believe it or not the water was colder in Grenada than it was in Jamaica. By the end of each 40min dive I was shivering with a shorty. Next time need a full suit like Wesley.

If some of you have been following me for a few years, you probably remember my time filming for my friend @anneofalltrades on her farm. 

Well there are no coincidences that I a few years later would get married to @cloudmotorsports, we would move onto a ton of land and start our own garden. It’s almost like deja vu. 

(But actually the way it really happened, was I had been telling Wes I wanted a garden for the longest time, and one day I came home to him on his tractor digging up a giant area of our yard. After the mild heart attack then realizing what was actually happening I was thrilled 😂)

But it’s funny because before I stepped foot on @anneofalltrades farm, I had not a clue what I was getting myself into. But boy did I learn a lot through all of the tutorial videos we filmed. 

But luckily for me, my husband Wes has a background in farming, so I serve as a great project manager 😉

We should have a few crops pop up here soon, and we are excited to be partially self sustainable. 

And no, the neighbors can’t hear my drums out here.

Sometime this drumming thing & keeping up with social media gets very exhausting. There are moments where I am not sure what I’m doing, or where I am going with this instrument, and I know I’m not alone in that. 

A lot of people have asked me in the past why I am not playing for any artists or touring, etc. The simple answer is in the video included in this post. Something can be your passion, but it doesn’t have to look like everyone else’s plan. Playing arenas doesn’t equal success for everyone. Maybe playing for your dog is your idea of success because that’s what makes you happy. 

Whatever your passion is, the most important thing is that you enjoy doing it, and make sure that when you are pursuing your passion, you are not burning yourself out. At the end of the day, you do not want to hate the thing that you once loved most, because when I was playing live shows that’s what slowly started to happen to me. What does your idea of success look like?

Balance is super important and I am learning every day to grow in and enjoy this instrument that has gotten me to achieve many great things and meet many great people along the way. 

Don’t stress, it’ll all fall into place. Just enjoy the drums.

September was one for the books! Started the month out with one of my photos of @anneofalltrades featured in Magnolia Magazine. Then a fun visit from our Canadian friends! We played card games, shot guns, enjoyed some bonfires, and had many laughs. After that @cloudmotorsports drove at LS Fest in Bowling Green Kentucky, which is always a good time. Got to then shoot photos with @libbydanforth which turned out amazing. Shortly after I went to visit my mom in South Carolina, and I was so grateful to spend time with her and enjoy the beautiful sights of Bluffton! Lastly, I was welcomed home after being gone for two weeks with the sweetest signage, hugs, balloons and kisses from Wes and puppy ❤️ Even got to see some hot air balloons at sunset 🌅 Looking forward to October 🍂🍁

A little behind the scenes action of my shoot with @libbydanforth a few weeks back! ✨🪩📸

Thank you all for being so patient as I navigate this busy season of life. Between a busy schedule, life changes, and a little bit of social media content creator burnout (if I’m honest), I really haven’t sat down to play drums in almost two months. I usually sit down and record 4-8 video clips at a time and release them throughout the coming weeks. I also have temporarily stopped doing the female features which I loved doing so much. 

But honestly right now I just don’t feel like it, and that’s ok! I feel like a break is always necessary. I’m the type of person that does something 110% or not at all, and I’m not wanting to half-ass my content just to post something new every day or keep up with whatever bs algorithm or frequency we’re expected to maintain 🙄 

Waiting for the right time to sit down and create new content again so it’s enjoyable for everyone. In due time I’ll get back into the groove of things but for now I am choosing to focus on family, my husband, and being in the present moment ❤️ 

Hope you all are taking care of yourselves, I’ll be back drumming again soon 😁

It is with a heavy heart that I share the news of the passing of my mother, Laura Lee DiLorenzo, who was called home by the Lord on Monday, November 27th, 2023 after her courageous two and a half year fight against cancer. Her strength and resilience throughout this journey were a testament to her unwavering faith. Her love touched countless lives, and her memory will forever live on in our hearts. We find solace in knowing she is now at peace in God's loving embrace. Details regarding a service to honor her life will be announced soon. Your prayers for our family during this very challenging time are deeply appreciated ❤️
